        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: honor plugin auth markers from manifests",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Honor plugin auth markers supplied by external manifests.\n- Keep auth-marker behavior covered in the agents test shard.\n- Preserve the fork-owned fix on fork `main` while offering this temporary branch for upstream review.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/model-auth-markers.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check`\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: Model/auth marker handling now respects marker metadata from external plugin manifests instead of dropping that manifest-provided signal.\n\nReal environment tested: Local OpenClaw source checkout on macOS at PR head `6100de63c389af2ba6eb2a9628b5d8340da7f756`; commands ran against the actual agents marker code.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/model-auth-markers.test.ts`; `git diff --check`.\n\nEvidence after fix: Terminal capture from the local OpenClaw checkout:\n\n```text\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/model-auth-markers.test.ts\n[test] starting test/vitest/vitest.agents.config.ts\nTest Files  1 passed (1)\nTests  9 passed (9)\n[test] passed 1 Vitest shard in 2.83s\n\n$ git diff --check\nexit status: 0\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: The manifest-auth-marker test shard exits 0 and confirms marker metadata is retained through the agents path.\n\nWhat was not tested: A live third-party plugin install was not run from this machine; this PR validates the manifest marker behavior with the repository's focused agents coverage.\n\n## Fork Context\n\nThis is a temporary upstream-review branch. The same accepted fix remains on `LDMB123/openclaw` fork `main`, per the fork cleanup plan.\n",
